The paper proposes a deep learning approach to graph partitioning, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the combinatorial nature of the problem, which suggests that it could also be categorized under algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper uses backpropagation to optimize the network parameters, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the generalizability of the proposed framework, which could also fall under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
